# Cursor rules — creation meta-policy (agent guide)

## Agent init

**Mandatory:** Read this entire section before any other content in this file; execute every `Action:` line here immediately and retain every `Rule:` and `Knowledge:` line for the rest of this session.

- Rule: Every bullet in **Rules content** is exactly one line starting with `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, or `Action:` — never wrap a rule across multiple lines.
- Rule: Type prefix is PascalCase with no spaces, first letter capitalized, followed by a colon and one space, then the statement — Example: `Knowledge: Tables in this file are reference material only.`
- Rule: `Knowledge:` bullets are context to read and retain; `Rule:` bullets are constraints to follow when this file applies; `Action:` bullets are steps to execute when their condition is met (init `Action:` bullets run now).
- Action: Read **Filters** (YAML above) to determine scope — `alwaysApply`, optional `globs`, and `description`.
- Action: After **Agent init**, read **Rules content** top to bottom; store every `Knowledge:` and `Rule:` bullet; run every `Action:` bullet per its text.

---

## Rules content

### Three sections (every rule file)

Every `.mdc` rule file uses exactly three sections in this order — **Filters**, **Agent init**, **Rules content** — apply when creating, adding, modifying, or editing any rule file.

- Knowledge: **Filters** is YAML frontmatter only — `description` (required), `alwaysApply` (required), optional `globs` when path-based attachment is needed.
- Knowledge: **Agent init** is the first markdown section the agent reads — one mandatory single-line opener, then typed bullets telling the agent how to read and apply the file.
- Knowledge: **Rules content** is the third and final section — header must be exactly `## Rules content`; it holds all enforceable and reference material; it may contain one or more `###` subsections.
- Rule: Do not add, rename, or reorder the three top-level sections — only **Rules content** may have nested `###` subsections.
- Rule: Default `alwaysApply` to `false` for intelligent use — set `true` only when the rule must load every session; omit `globs` unless the user explicitly requests path filters.

### Rules content subsections

Each `###` subsection under **Rules content** groups related bullets; apply this format when authoring or editing any rule file including this meta-policy.

- Knowledge: Every `###` subsection starts with exactly one instruction line (not a bullet) telling the agent what the group covers and when to use it.
- Knowledge: Below the instruction line, list every rule as a bullet using `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, or `Action:` — one statement per bullet.
- Rule: A **Rules content** file must have at least one `###` subsection with at least one typed bullet.
- Rule: Markdown tables are allowed only inside a `###` subsection, after the instruction line and after a `Knowledge:` bullet that introduces the table.
- Knowledge: Nested sub-subsections (`####`) are discouraged — prefer additional `###` groups with their own instruction line and bullets.

### Agent init authoring

Apply when writing or reviewing the **Agent init** section of any rule file.

- Rule: The mandatory opener in **Agent init** is exactly one line — format: `**Mandatory:**` followed by one sentence telling the agent to read the section and how to treat `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, and `Action:` bullets.
- Rule: Every bullet under the mandatory opener uses the typed prefix format — `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, or `Action:` — one statement per bullet.
- Rule: The first bullet after the mandatory opener must be a `Rule:` line restating that all **Rules content** bullets are single-line `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, or `Action:` statements.
- Knowledge: **Agent init** bullets tell the agent how to read the file — store-for-later bullets use `Knowledge:` or `Rule:`; execute-now bullets use `Action:`.

### Filename and template

Apply when scaffolding a new rule file or validating an existing path under `.cursor/rules/`.

- Rule: Filename `<name>.mdc` is one lowercase word matching `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$`, length 2–32; single-topic rules live at **`.cursor/rules/<name>/<name>.mdc`**; reserved names `rules`, `constants`, `solution`, `template` are forbidden outside **`.cursor/rules/rules/`** and their own **`.cursor/rules/<name>/`** folders.
- Rule: This meta-policy governs creation and structural edits of `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc` files — use normal editing for content-only updates that already match this layout.
- Action: When creating a new rule file, copy **`.cursor/rules/rules/template.mdc`** to the target path — do not invent structure from scratch.
- Action: When a rule needs project or AWS parameter values, link **`.cursor/rules/constants/constants.mdc`** by constant ID — never paste literal `PRJ_*`, account, profile, or region values.
- Action: When the user wants guided creation, run **`skills/rules-create/SKILL.md`** (via **`.cursor/skills/ray-test/SKILL.md`** if skill choice is unclear) in parallel with this file.
- Knowledge: Canonical scaffold — **`.cursor/rules/rules/template.mdc`**.
- Knowledge: Mature rule example — **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-naming.mdc`** (migrate toward this layout when materially editing).

### Creation intake

Apply during interactive creation of a new rule file via skill or manual scaffold.

- Rule: Collect new **Rules content** bullets one at a time — after each bullet ask **"Next rule, or `finished`?"** until the user replies `finished`.
- Rule: Remove all `REPLACE_ME`, HTML comments, and template placeholders before saving.
- Rule: Split into a second `.mdc` file when scope exceeds ~200 lines — add a `Knowledge:` bullet in **Related** naming the sibling file.
- Action: Confirm the user wants a **new** rule file — if the target path exists, ask before overwrite; on decline, stop or restart at name collection.
- Action: Collect `rule_name`, `rule_purpose`, `description`, `alwaysApply`, optional `globs`, H1 title, **Agent init** content, and **Rules content** subsections before writing.
- Action: After creation, output **only** the Handoff table in the subsection below — no extra narrative.

### Handoff (creation output only)

Emit only when finishing creation of a new rule file — not when editing or reading.

- Knowledge: After creating a new rule file, output only this table:

| Field | Value |
|-------|--------|
| **File** | target `.mdc` path |
| **Sections** | Filters · Agent init · Rules content |
| **When** | Bulleted triggers (max 3–5) |
| **How** | Bulleted usage steps (max 3–5) |
| **alwaysApply** | `true` or `false` |
| **globs** | Patterns or `—` if omitted |
| **Rules (concise)** | First few words after each `Knowledge:` / `Rule:` / `Action:` bullet |
| **Totals** | Bullets: *n* · Lines: *approx* · alwaysApply: *yes/no* |

### Edge cases

Apply when creation or editing encounters ambiguity — resolve before writing.

- Knowledge: User gives multiple bullets at once — accept but verify each is one typed single-line bullet before write.
- Knowledge: User asks for `globs` — add YAML `globs` list; keep `alwaysApply: false` unless user also wants always-on.
- Knowledge: Edit existing rule — refactor in place toward the three-section layout when materially editing; do not run creation intake unless adding a new file.

### Related

Reference paths for linked rules and skills — link by path; do not duplicate constant values here.

- Knowledge: Guided creation skill — **`skills/rules-create/SKILL.md`** (router: **`.cursor/skills/ray-test/SKILL.md`**).
- Knowledge: Project constants — **`.cursor/rules/constants/constants.mdc`**.
- Knowledge: Documentation README policy — **`.cursor/rules/docs/docs.mdc`**.
- Knowledge: Solution scope and ports — **`.cursor/rules/solution/solution.mdc`**.
